A 48-month-old cow that died has been confirmed as having had mad cow disease the country's Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries Ministry said Thursday.
The Japan National Institution of Infectious Disease confirmed the infection after conducting detailed checks on samples from the cow, which tested positive Monday in an initial examination.
Tests confirm Irish case of human form of mad cow disease.
One person, a woman who had lived in Britain, was diagnosed with the disease in the Republic.
The human form of mad cow disease is called variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob.
